@jsumners Getting started example also uses `async` function for db connector, is it wrong too?

```js
// our-db-connector.js
const MongoClient = require('mongodb').MongoClient

async function db (fastify, options) {
  const url = options.url
  delete options.url

  const db = await MongoClient.connect(url, options)
  fastify.decorate('mongo', db)
}

module.exports = db
```

@dolphin278 I think so. The `.register` method is really just `middie` under the hood. And I don't see where `middie` accommodates promises at all:

https://github.com/fastify/middie/blob/2ac769a0a64e396de5d2d08990e82863a154f3cd/middie.js#L81-L91

@delvedor @mcollina am I wrong?
